                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/98: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-02T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 2, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 2—6:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>782. Legation’s 775, September 28, 8 p.m. Following from Counselor of Legation at
                    Nanking to the Legation and Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 30, 9 a.m. Ingram and I called on the Director of the
                            Department of Internal [<hi rend="italic">International</hi>] Affairs
                            September 29, 4 p.m. and protested in sense of your paragraph 1. After
                            lengthy discussion the Director agreed to telegraph the Inspector
                            General of Foreign Affairs at Canton that the two Legations had again
                            formally protested against the application of form to American and
                            British companies but might possibly consent to their respective
                            companies applying for registration if all reference to restriction of
                            output and business tax were deleted from application form. Fuller
                            report by mail.<note n="94" xml:id="d627fn94">Not printed.</note>”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
